The musical score was composed by [[Vishal<U+2013>Shekhar]], and the lyrics for the film's six songs{{efn|The title song "Kahaani" features twice in the film.}} were written by Vishal Dadlani, Anvita Dutt and Sandeep Srivasta. Several of [[R. D. Burman]]'s Hindi and Bengali compositions were used in the background. An album of the music was released on 22 February 2012.

The soundtrack received positive reviews, and was praised for its amalgamation of Bengali and Hindi lyrics. A review in [[CNN-IBN]] states that the song "Ami Shotti Bolchi" is able to partially convey the feel of Kolkata, and that the soundtrack "features right voices as per the overall mood of the album."<ref>{{cite news
|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/music-review-kahaani-focuses-on-nostalgia/232715-45-76.html
