==Marketing and release==
''Kahaani''{{'}}s first-look poster was launched on 2 December 2011,<ref>{{cite news
|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Bollywood/FIRST-LOOK-Vidya-Balan-in-Kahaani/Article1-776399.aspx
|title=First look: Vidya Balan in ''Kahaani''
|newspaper=Hindustan Times
|accessdate=4 May 2012
|date=2 December 2011
}}</ref> and the official trailer on 5 January 2012.<ref>{{cite news
|url=http://www.ndtv.com/video/player/news/first-look-of-vidya-balans-i-kahaani-i-launched/220329?sp
|title=First look of Vidya Balan's ''Kahaani'' launched
|publisher=NDTV
|accessdate=4 May 2012
|date=5 January 2012
}}</ref> The poster, portraying a pregnant Vidya Balan and lacking any romantic element, was well received. Critics' expectations were low, owing to the director's previous box-office failures.<ref name="ibn rathnam 28march" /> Balan appeared in public with a prosthetic belly to promote the film, and mingled with the public in railway stations, bus stands and markets.<ref name=ZNpromotion>{{cite web
|url=http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/celebrity/vidya-s-arnab-bagchi-found_107140.htm
|title=Vidya's Arnab Bagchi found!
|publisher=Zee News
|accessdate=26 March 2012
|date=6 March 2012
}}</ref><ref>{{cite news
|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-03-05/news-interviews/31123542_1_kahaani-vidya-balan-pregnant-woman
|title=Vidya Balan to promote ''Kahaani'' in Ahmedabad
|first=Tanvi
|last=Trivedi
|newspaper=The Times of India
|agency=TNN
|accessdate=9 April 2012
|date=5 March 2012
}}</ref> She often carried a sketch of her on-screen missing husband, and asked people to help in finding him.<ref name=ZNpromotion/><ref name="Vidya Story @ TT">{{cite news
|url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1120305/jsp/entertainment/story_15211741.jsp#.UZ7uTrVQHzw
