''Kahaani'' garnered generally positive reviews from critics. According to review aggregator [[ReviewGang]] the film received a rating of 7.5 out of 10,<ref>{{cite web
|url=http://www.reviewgang.com/movies/225-Kahaani-Review
|title=''Kahaani'' movie review
|publisher=[[ReviewGang]]
|accessdate=9 March 2012
}}</ref> based on the reviews by professional critics. Good word of mouth publicity played a part in its popularity besides the positive reviews.<ref>{{cite news
|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-03-19/news-interviews/31209950_1_box-office-starrer-release
|title=Word-of-mouth promos pay off at box office
|last=Dubey
|first=Bharati
|date=19 March 2012
|accessdate=23 March 2013
|work=The Times of India}}</ref><ref>{{cite web
|url=http://movies.ndtv.com/bollywood/kahaani-paan-singh-tomar-on-a-roll-at-box-office-187827
|title=''Kahaani'', ''Paan Singh Tomar'' on a roll at box office
|publisher=NDTV
|date=20 March 2012
|accessdate=23 March 2013}}</ref> ''[[The Telegraph (Calcutta)|The Telegraph]]'' called the film "a mind-juggling medley of manipulation masquerading as a 'mother of a story'".<ref name="telegraph review">{{cite news
|url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1120310/jsp/entertainment/story_15231247.jsp#.T3F0dEoQgrU
|title=What a ''Kahaani''
|first=Pratim D.
|last=Gupta
|newspaper=The Telegraph
|accessdate=27 March 2012
|date=10 March 2012
|location=Calcutta, India
}}</ref> [[Taran Adarsh]] of [[Bollywood Hungama]] gave the film 4 out of 5 stars, and praised Balan's acting.<ref name="bh score">{{cite web
|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/criticreview/id/542221|publisher=Bollywood Hungama
|title=''Kahaani'' movie review
|first=Taran
|last=Adarsh
|accessdate=8 March 2012
|date=8 March 2012
}}</ref> ''[[The Times of India]]'' commented "Once again, a 'pregnant' Vidya, ironically displays more 'male ornaments'&nbsp;... than most heroes."<ref name="toi review">{{cite news
|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/hindi/Kahaani/movie-review/12188039.cms
|title=''Kahaani'' movie review
|first=Madhureeta
|last=Mukherjee
|newspaper=The Times of India
|accessdate=8 March 2012
|date=8 March 2012
}}</ref> The reviews in [[Rediff]],<ref name="rediff Review">{{cite web
|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/review-vidya-balan-rocks-in-kahaani/20120309.htm
|title=Review: Vidya Balan rocks in ''Kahaani''
|first=Sukanya
|last=Verma
|publisher=Rediff
|accessdate=9 March 2012
|date=9 March 2012
}}</ref> [[Indo-Asian News Service|Indo Asian News Service]],<ref name="ians score">{{cite news
|url=http://movies.ndtv.com/movie_review.aspx?id=689
|title=Review: ''Kahaani''
|first=Subhash K.
|last=Jha
|publisher=NDTV
|agency=IANS
|accessdate=5 April 2012
|date=9 March 2012
}}</ref> CNN-IBN,<ref name="cnnibn score">{{cite news
|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/masand-a-taut-kahaani-is-a-delicious-thriller/237674-47-84.html
|title=Masand: A taut ''Kahaani'' is a delicious thriller
|first=Rajeev
|last=Masand
|publisher=CNN-IBN
|accessdate=5 April 2012
|date=10 March 2012
}}</ref> Zee News,<ref name="ZeeNews">{{cite web
|url=http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/movies/review-vidya-kolkata-in-a-never-seen-before-avatar-in-kahaani_107278.htm
|title=Review: Vidya, Kolkata in a never-seen-before avatar in ''Kahaani''
|first=Shomini
|last=Sen
|publisher=Zee News
|accessdate=10 March 2012
|date=10 March 2012
}}</ref> ''[[Hindustan Times]]'',<ref name="choprahindustan">{{cite news
|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Reviews/Anupama-Chopra-s-review-Kahaani/Article1-823366.aspx
|title=Anupama Chopra's review: ''Kahaani''
|first=Anupama
|last=Chopra
|newspaper=Hindustan Times
|accessdate=17 March 2012
|date=10 March 2012
}}</ref> and ''[[The Hindu]]''<ref name="hindu review">{{cite news
|url=http://www.thehindu.com/life-and-style/nxg/article2994454.ece
|title=''Kahaani''<U+2014>Twists in the tale
|first=Balaji
|last=Ravi
|newspaper=The Hindu
|accessdate=14 March 2012
|date=14 March 2012
|location=Chennai, India
}}</ref> were unanimously positive, and noted script, direction, cinematography, and acting as strong points of the film. Noted film actress and multiple [[National Film Awards|National Award]] winner [[Shabana Azmi]] lauded Balan for her performance,"As an actor, I could see she [Balan] was making all the right moves throughout the film. There was not a single artificial note in her performance."<ref>{{cite news
|url=http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/movies/vidya-should-avoid-pitfall-of-doing-central-parts-shabana_107995.htm
|title=Vidya should avoid pitfall of doing central parts: Shabana
|publisher=Zee News
|agency=IANS
|accessdate=21 March 2012
|date=21 March 2012
}}</ref> Russell Edwards, the reviewer for ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'', praised the cast, cinematography, and direction, and commented that despite occasional glitches, the "adroit thriller&nbsp;... maintains momentum and credibility."<ref>{{cite news|url=http://variety.com/2012/film/reviews/kahaani-1117947230/|title='Kahaani'|last=Edwards|first=Russell|date=12 March 2012|accessdate=21 March 2013|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]}}</ref>

Many reviewers criticised the film's climax and certain features, feeling that they deviated from its general style. Rituparna Chatterjee of CNN-IBN noted that the climax of the film was a "huge dampener" and explained, "The diabolic twist at that juncture got underplayed&nbsp;... What follows is a sobfest&nbsp;... the apologetic explanation of why she does what she does. Justifying her action comes across more as an effort to appease the Indian morality"<ref name="chatterjeeibn3122012">{{cite web
|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/kahaani-why-the-film-doesnt-work-for-me/238393-8-66.html
|title=''Kahaani'': Why the film doesn't work for me
|first=Rituparna
|last=Chatterjee
|publisher=CNN-IBN
|accessdate=15 March 2012
|date=12 March 2012
}}</ref> The ''[[Outlook (magazine)|Outlook]]'' review noted, "At times, ''Kahaani'' is too clever, at others extremely pedestrian like in the depiction of computer hacking and IB operations, not to speak of the ludicrous terrorist angle and the all-too predictable Durga Puja setting for that mythology tie-in."<ref name="joshioutlook">{{cite web
|url=http://www.outlookindia.com/article.aspx?280230
|title=Movie review: ''Kahaani''
|first=Namrata
|last=Joshi
|work=[[Outlook (magazine)|Outlook]]
|accessdate=17 March 2012
|date=26 March 2012
}}</ref> It adds that the "spoon-feeding" of reasons at the end dampens the intrigue factor.<ref name="joshioutlook"/> The review in [[Yahoo!|Yahoo! India]] comments that the Durga metaphor at the end was enforced, and that the film over-indulged in Bengali stereotypes.<ref name="yahoo review">{{cite web|url=http://in.movies.yahoo.com/blogs/movie-reviews/kahaani-review-190252653.html|title=Kahaani review|last=Guha|first=Kunal|publisher=Yahoo India| date=8 March 2012|accessdate=22 March 2013}}</ref> Gautaman Bhaskaran, in his review in ''[[Gulf Times]]'', noted that the sometimes-handheld photography was "as irksome as the plot with a sleuth too many and cops galore."<ref name="gautaman gt 14 March 2012">{{cite news
|url= http://www.gautamanbhaskaran.com/gb/images/joy.pdf
|title=The story of ''Kahaani''
|first=Gautaman
|last=Bhaskaran
|newspaper=Gulf Times
|format=PDF
|page=6
|accessdate=15 March 2013
|date=14 March 2012
}}</ref>

Though ''Kahaani'' received critical acclaim, it was a slow starter at the box office, opening to a poor response on the first day,<ref name="BO1">{{cite web
|url=http://boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4138&nCat=
|title=''Kahaani'' Friday business
|publisher=Box Office India
|accessdate= 24 may 2013
|date=10 March 2012
}}</ref><ref name="BO2">{{cite web
|url=http://boxofficeindia.com/npages.php?page=shownews&articleid=4129&nCat=
|title='Kahaani'' expected to lead ''Chaar Din Ki Chandni''
|publisher=Box Office India
|accessdate=24 May 2013
|date=7 March 2012
}}</ref> but gradually picking afterwards.<ref name="BO3">{{cite web
|url=http://boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4171&nCat=
|title=''Kahaani'' is super hit: Heads for 45<U+2013>50 crore
|publisher=Box Office India
|accessdate=5 April 2012
|date=18 March 2012
}}</ref> According to ''The Telegraph'', the film earned almost {{INRConvert|20|m}} from the state of West Bengal within the first three days of its release. At multiplexes in Kolkata, occupancy increased from 47% on Friday 9 March, the day of release, to 77% on 10 March and to around 97% on 11 March.<ref name="BO bullseye @ TT">{{cite news
|url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1120313/jsp/calcutta/story_15241893.jsp
|title='Bidya' hits BO bullseye&nbsp;<U+2014> Calcutta's ''Kahaani'' is a word-of-mouth rage
|first=Priyanka
|last=Roy
|newspaper=The Telegraph
|accessdate=22 May 2012
|date=13 March 2012
|location=Calcutta, India
}}</ref> [[Box Office India]], a website on Indian film trade, reported that the film collected nearly {{INRConvert|240|m}} in its first week, well beyond its production cost of {{INRConvert|80|m}}.<ref>{{cite web
|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/overdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4174&nCat=
|title=Kahaani Week One Territorial Breakdown
|publisher=Box Office India
|accessdate=19 March 2012
|date=19 March 2012
}}</ref> It grossed {{INRConvert|190|m}} in second week to make a two-week total of around {{INRConvert|430|m}} in India;<ref>{{cite web
|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/overdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4202&nCat=
|title=Kahaani Week Two Territorial Breakdown
|publisher=[[Box Office India]]
|accessdate=26 March 2012
|date=26 March 2012
}}</ref> this led Box Office India to declare the film a "Super Hit".<ref>{{cite web
|url=http://boxofficeindia.com/boxdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4192&nCat=
|title=''Agent Vinod'' average opening ''Kahaani'' extraordinary week two
|publisher=Box Office India
|accessdate=24 March 2012
|date=24 March 2012
}}</ref> The film was successful in the international box office as well, garnering {{INRConvert|80|m}} within 10 days of its release in seven markets<U+2014>UK, US, UAE, Australia, New Zealand, Malaysia and Pakistan, according to Bollywood Hungama, a film-related website.<ref name="adarsh overseas 20-3">{{cite web
|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/trade/boxofficeoverseas/id/412
|title=''Kahaani'' overtakes ''TDP'' in overseas
|first=Taran
|last=Adarsh
|publisher=Bollywood Hungama
|accessdate=8 May 2012
|date=20 March 2012
}}</ref> By the third week, according to CNN-IBN, it had grossed {{INRConvert|750|m}}, including India and overseas market.<ref name="75crore@IBN">{{cite web
|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/kahaani-grosses-rs-75-crore-at-the-box-office/242076-8-66.html
|title=''Kahaani'' grosses Rs 75 crore at the box office: The story behind the numbers
|publisher=CNN-IBN
|accessdate= 23 March 2012
|date=23 March 2012
}}</ref><ref>{{cite web
|url=http://www.firstpost.com/bollywood/kahaani-whats-the-story-behind-the-numbers-253056.html
|title=''Kahaani'': What's the story behind the numbers?
|publisher=Firstpost
|accessdate=22 March 2012
|date=22 March 2012
}}</ref> ''Hindustan Times'' reported that ''Kahaani'' made a worldwide gross of {{INRConvert|1044.3|m}} within 50 days of its release.<ref name="ht 50 gross"/>

''Kahaani'' was nominated for, and won, many awards. At the [[58th Filmfare Awards]], it was nominated for five awards, including Best Actress for Balan and Best Director for Ghosh; it won all five.<ref>{{cite web|
title=58th Idea Filmfare Awards nominations are here!
|url=http://www.filmfare.com/news/58th-idea-filmfare-awards-nominations-are-here-2123.html
|publisher=Filmfare
|date=13 January 2013
|accessdate=23 January 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web
|title=Winners of 58th Idea Filmfare Awards 2012
|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/celebrities/features/type/view/id/4432
|publisher=Bollywood Hungama
|date=20 January 2013
|accessdate=23 January 2013}}</ref> The film was nominated for thirteen awards at the [[Screen Awards|19th&nbsp;Colors Screen Awards]], and won five, including Best Actress and Best Story.<ref>{{cite web
|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/4403
|title=Winners of 19th Annual Colors Screen Awards
|publisher=Bollywood Hungama | date=12 January 2013
|accessdate=24 May 2013}}</ref> At the [[Zee Cine Awards|14th Zee Cine Awards]], ''Kahaani'' won five awards, including Best Film (Critics) and Best Actress (Critics).<ref>{{cite web
|title=Nominations for Zee Cine Awards 2013
|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/4349
|publisher=Bollywood Hungama
|date=29 December 2012
|accessdate=4 January 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web
|title=Winners of Zee Cine Awards 2013
|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/4376/Winners+of+Zee+Cine+Awards+2013
|publisher=Bollywood Hungama
|accessdate=14 January 2013}}</ref> In the [[60th National Film Awards|60th iteration]] of India's [[National Film Awards]], Ghosh won [[National Film Award for Best Screenplay|Best Screenplay (Original)]], Namrata Rao won [[National Film Award for Best Editing|Best Editing]], and Nawazuddin Siddiqui won a [[National Film Award&nbsp;<U+2013> Special Jury Award / Special Mention (Feature Film)|Special Jury]] award.<ref>{{cite web
|title=60th National Film Awards: The list of winners&nbsp;<U+2013> IBN Live
|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/60th-national-film-awards-the-list-of-winners/379590-8-66.html
|publisher=CNN-IBN
|accessdate=19 March 2013|date=18 March 2013}}</ref>

==Impact==

Following ''Kahaani''{{'}}s success, Kolkata became a preferred destination for [[Bollywood]] filmmakers.<ref name="abp 31aug12">{{cite web
|url=http://www.anandabazar.com/archive/1120831/31binodan1.html
|title='Kolkata ghure ponchash dine "Gunde" gorbe Yashraj'
|trans_title=Yashraj will make "Gunde" in Kolkata in fifty days
|first=Indranil
|last=Roy
|work=Anandabazar Patrika
|language=Bengali
|accessdate=31 August 2012
|date=31 August 2012}}</ref><ref name="ht limelight">{{cite news|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Bollywood/Kahaani-brings-Kolkata-back-to-limelight/Article1-824119.aspx|title=Kahaani brings Kolkata back to limelight|date= 12 March 2012|newspaper=Hindustan Times|accessdate=20 March 2013}}</ref> They felt the landscapes of Mumbai and Delhi were overused for several decades, while Kolkata retained its unique visuals such as [[metro train]]s, rickety trams, [[Pulled rickshaw|hand-pulled rickshaws]], dingy bylanes, British-era buildings, and iconic structures including [[Howrah Bridge]] and [[Victoria Memorial (India)|Victoria Memorial]].<ref name=Kolkata_Limelight@ZN>{{cite news
|url=http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/movies/kahaani-brings-kolkata-back-to-limelight_107407.htm
|title=''Kahaani'' brings Kolkata back to limelight
|publisher=Zee News
|agency=PTI
|accessdate=30 March 2012
|date=11 March 2012
}}</ref> 

Monalisa Guest House, the lodge which hosted Vidya Bagchi in the film, became a local attraction.<ref>{{cite news
|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Bollywood/Single-screen-theatres-resurface-to-tell-Vidya-s-Kahaani/Article1-835430.aspx
|title=Single screen theatres resurface to tell Vidya's ''Kahaani''
|newspaper=Hindustan Times
|agency=IANS
|accessdate=5 April 2012
|date=4 April 2012
}}</ref> Several hundreds have visited it since the film's release, to the extent that the owners planned to increase tariffs and renovate the rooms around a ''Kahaani'' theme.<ref name="StarChamber">{{cite news
|url=http://www.business-standard.com/india/news/star-chamber/468894/
|title=Star chamber
|first=Probal
|last=Basak
|newspaper=[[Business Standard]]
|accessdate=26 March 2012
|date=25 March 2012
}}</ref>

The potbellied contract-killer Bob Biswas became an [[internet phenomenon]], the subject of several jokes and pieces of [[pop art]], which circulated through Facebook and Twitter.<ref name="pheno 1 ndtv">{{cite news
|url=http://movies.ndtv.com/movie_story.aspx?Section=Movies&ID=ENTEN20120198515&subcatg=MOVIESINDIA&keyword=bollywood&nid=193308
|title=''Kahaani's'' Bob Biswas a rage on FB, Twitter
|publisher=NDTV
|agency=PTI
|accessdate=10 April 2012
|date=3 April 2012
}}</ref> "Nomoshkar, Aami Bob Biswas... Ek minute?" ("Hello, I am Bob Biswas... do you have a minute?")<U+2014>the monologue he repeatedly uses just before murdering his victims<U+2014>was used in different [[internet meme|memes]].<ref name="pheno 3 ibn"/> A [[graphic novel]] and a television show based on Bob Biswas were being planned, as of March 2012.<ref name="pheno 4 toi">{{cite news
|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-03-22/news-interviews/31224239_1_sujoy-ghosh-fan-frenzy-character
|title=Pop art on Saswata Chatterjee's character
|first=Roshni
|last=Mukherjee
|newspaper=The Times of India
|agency=TNN
|accessdate=10 April 2012
|date=22 March 2012
}}</ref><ref name="pheno 5 toi">{{cite news
|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/bengali/news-interviews/Bob-Biswas-now-on-TV/articleshow/12633763.cms
|title=Bob Biswas now on TV
|first=Subhash K.
|last=Jha
|newspaper=The Times of India
|agency=TNN
|accessdate=12 April 2012
|date=12 April 2012
}}</ref>

In March 2012, Sujoy Ghosh announced that he intended to develop ''Kahaani'' into a series. He was inspired by Satyajit Ray's ''[[Feluda]]'' detective series and wanted to continue the stories of Vidya Bagchi on similar lines, with Balan reprising the role.<ref name="Jha franchise">{{cite news
|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-03-16/news-interviews/31200857_1_sujoy-ghosh-s-kahaani-vidya-balan-franchise
|title=''Kahaani'' to be a franchise?
|first=Subhash K.
|last= Jha
|newspaper=The Times of India
|accessdate=27 March 2012
|date=16 March 2012
}}</ref> The shooting of ''Kahaani 2'' is scheduled to begin in 2013.<ref name="Kahaani 2 shooting schedule">{{cite news
|last=IANS
|title=''Kahaani 2'' with Vidya Balan will hit the floors in 2013
|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/kahaani-2-shooting-to-start-in-2013/296067-8-66.html
|publisher=CNN-IBN
|accessdate=28 September 2012
|date=24 May 2013
}}</ref> As of May 2012, two remakes of ''Kahaani'' in [[Tamil language|Tamil]] and [[Telugu language|Telugu]] are planned; [[Sekhar Kammula]] is slated to direct, and [[Nayantara]] will play the lead role.<ref name="ibn 52012 remake">{{cite news
|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/tamil-remake-for-bollywood-blockbuster-kahaani/259591-71-180.html
|title=Tamil remake for Bollywood blockbuster ''Kahaani''
|publisher=CNN-IBN
|accessdate=20 May 2012
|date=20 May 2012
}}</ref>

